411	/// Idempotently install throwaway RBRR prefixes into `.rbk/rbrr.env`.
412	///
413	/// Pristine-lifecycle cases that need non-blank prefixes (depot/governor/
414	/// retriever/director lifecycle) call this as their first step. The helper
415	/// reads current values; if `RBRR_CLOUD_PREFIX` and `RBRR_RUNTIME_PREFIX`
416	/// already match the throwaway markers, returns `Ok(())` with no side
417	/// effect. Otherwise rewrites both lines in place, then `git add` +
418	/// `git commit` the change. One commit per fixture run regardless of which
419	/// case is the first to call it.
420	///
421	/// HEAD walks off marshal-zero after the commit; recovery is `rbw-MZ`,
